import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.plot(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = data['id'].astype(str)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data.groupby('id')['rate'].apply(list), showfliers=False)
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['id'].unique())
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['rate'], data['GDP'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between unemployment rate and GDP?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = data['id'].astype(str)
    data = data.groupby('id').mean()
    data = data.reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate for each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Average Unemployment Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate_change'] = data.groupby('id')['rate'].pct_change()
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['id'])
    data['rate_change'] = data['rate_change'] * 100
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['id'], data['rate_change'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region ID')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percentage Change in Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the percentage change in unemployment rate for each region?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
